    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 21-SI SERIES - REASSEMBLY - STATOR</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="1">
        <title>STATOR</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0801728">Figure 28</hotlnk>
            for Item numbers in parentheses.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0801728" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0801728" filename="../figg08/g0801728.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Installing Stator</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. STATOR</callout1>
                <callout1>2. RECTIFIER BRIDGE NUTS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. PHASE LEADS</callout1>
                <callout1>4. THREADED STUDS ON RECTIFIER BRIDGE</callout1>
                <callout1>5. SRE HOUSING ASSEMBLY</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install stator (Item 1) into SRE housing assembly (Item 5). Place 3 phase leads (Item 3)
                over 3 threaded studs on rectifier bridge (Item 4). Be sure stator is seated in register around edge of
                SRE housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install rectifier bridge nuts (Item 2) to 3 threaded studs on rectifier bridge (Item 4).
                Tighten rectifier bridge nuts (3 places) to 22 in-lb (2.5 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
